Barcelona have reportedly identified a ‘Plan B’ if they are unable to sign Erling Haaland from Borussia Dortmund this summer. The Norwegian striker is expected to be one of the most sought-after players in world football in the next transfer window. Haaland has a £68m release clause which comes into effect this summer, with some of Europe’s biggest clubs including Real Madrid and Manchester City also keen. Champions League: Chelsea 1, Lille 0 Mourinho Hit With Ban After Roma Outburst Caused Controversy The alternative option up front would be Real Sociedad striker Alexander Isak. Isak, 22, has been linked with a host of clubs over the last two transfer windows after an impressive year for club and country this season However, the 22-year-old has scored just four goals in 20 LaLiga appearances comparing to the 17 he netted in 34 games last season.